                <note xml:id="SUNREDWAVESGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;And quick as sun&#x2010;red waves&#x201D; (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVIII">MS VIII</title>; 
                    <title type="book" corresp="#JRPOEMS1891"><hi rend="italic">Poems</hi></title> [<date when="1891">1891</date>]; <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Works</hi></title> [<date when="1903">1903</date>])&#x2014;</hi><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> 
                    initially wrote &#x201C;sunwaves&#x201D; as a single word, and then he placed a caret between &#x201C;sun&#x201D; and &#x201C;waves&#x201D; and inserted above the line &#x201C;&#x2010;red&#x201D; to form &#x201C;sun&#x2010;red waves&#x201D;. 
                    <persName corresp="#WGC">Collingwood</persName> mistranscribed the insertion as &#x201C;sunned&#x201D;, and the editors of the <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE">Library Edition</title> 
                    adopted that reading.</p></note>
